_ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="ng-tns-c243-10 ng-star-inserted" style=""><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> 1 Prices for Mutual Funds are not updated until after market close (typically around 7pm ET). </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> 2 The Market Value Change is the difference between the most recent market value and the previous day market value. Market Value is the product of Quantity and Last Price. For Mutual Funds, the most recent Market Value Change is retained throughout the day until prices are updated in the evening, typically around 7pm ET. MV Change for Fixed Income holdings occurs only when there is an intraday purchase or sale. </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10 ng-star-inserted"> 3 Distributed to Paid-In Capital: is a measure of the cumulative value of distributions paid to the investors in a private equity fund relative to the money invested (i.e. cash-on-cash). DPI is expressed as a multiple of investors' paid-in investment capital. DPI adds to RVPI to determine the Total Value to Paid-in Capital (TVPI) of the fund. </p><!----><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10 ng-star-inserted"> 4 Multiple on Invested Capital: is a metric used to describe the value or performance of an investment relative to its initial cost, commonly used within private markets. MOIC is among the most relevant metrics to be assessed while conducting fund due diligence. It is also often referred to as Equity Multiple. </p><!----><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> Real-time or Delayed pricing of holdings is for domestic equities and options only. Pricing of other positions is as of the previous day's close, or the most recently available price. Positions are priced as of the last trade. The current bid or ask may be different from the price displayed. </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> Intraday Holdings do not account for orders that are executed but have not yet been reported by the exchanges/market makers. Please check your orders before placing trades. </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> Last Price represents the price at which the last trade occurred. </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10">Accrued Interest calculated as of previous business day.</p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> Quote data delayed per exchange agreement - Data delayed at least 15 minutes for NYSE, AMEX, NASDAQ, OTC, OTCBB and OPRA. </p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10">For valuation, delayed quotes using the last price are used for domestic equities and options only. Pricing of other positions is as of the previous day's close or the most recently available price. If an equity security has not traded today, the valuation is based on the best bid price from the previous business day. The current bid or ask may be different from the price displayed. Securities pricing may vary from actual liquidation value.</p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10">Prices shown should only be used as a general guide to portfolio value. Your printed confirmations and statements are the official records of your account.</p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10">The value of any non-dollar denominated holding used is first converted in to a U.S. Dollar Equivalent (USDE) amount. The USDE amount is calculated by multiplying the previous day's closing price for the holding in its native currency by the previous day's closing spot (conversion) rate from sources deemed to be reliable. If the previous day's closing price is not available, then the most recent closing price available for the holding will be used.</p><p _ngcontent-aho-c243="" class="disclaimer ng-tns-c243-10"> Unrealized Gain/Loss value is based on positions and quotes as of previous close. </p></div><!----></div><!----></div></main><!----><!----></app-portfolio><!----></div></main></div></div></div><!----><!----></div><app-footer _ngcontent-aho-c164="" _nghost-aho-c155="" class="ng-tns-c155-9 ng-tns-c164-4 ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-aho-c155="" class="footer ng-tns-c155-9"><div _ngcontent-aho-c155="" class="wrap ng-tns-c155-9"><div _ngcontent-aho-c155="" class="wrap-top ng-tns-c155-9" style="padding-bottom: 24px;"><div _ngcontent-aho-c155="" class="copyright ng-tns-c155-9"><span _ngcontent-aho-c155="" class="ng-tns-c155-9"> © 2026 BTG Pactual US Capital, LLC. Nothing in this webpage should be construed as a solicitation, offer or recommendation to acquire or dispose of any investment or to engage in any other transaction. The investor must read all documents available from the issuer of the securities that he/she holds, including but not limited to fact sheets, offering circulars, and pricing supplements. BTG Pactual primarily buys and sells securities on behalf of its customers. Each time a customer enters into a buy or sell transaction, BTG Pactual may charge a commission, referral fee, and/or subscription fee. In addition, there are distribution fees and fees assessed to clear and settle transactions.
